<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Bug Report</title>

  <style>
    /* ===== Base layout ===== */
    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 40px;
      font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #0d0d0d;
      color: #e6e6e6;
    }

    .page {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      background: #1a1a1a;
      border: 1px solid #2e2e2e;
      padding: 32px 36px;
    }

    /* ===== Headings ===== */
    h2 {
      margin-top: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #2e2e2e;
      padding-bottom: 4px;
      cursor: pointer;
      color: #f2f2f2;
    }

    h2::after {
      content: "▼";
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      margin-left: 6px;
      opacity: 0.7;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    h2.collapsed::after {
      transform: rotate(-90deg);
    }

    /* ===== Section content ===== */
    .section-content {
      margin-top: 10px;
    }

    /* ===== Lists & text ===== */
    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #dcdcdc;
    }

    ul, ol {
      margin: 8px 0 8px 20px;
      padding: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin: 4px 0;
      color: #d0d0d0;
    }

    strong {
      color: #ffffff;
    }

    /* ===== Links ===== */
    a {
      color: #6ba4ff;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    /* ===== Bug Form (exact same UI style) ===== */
    .bug-form {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 16px;
      background: #1a1a1a;
      border: 1px solid #2e2e2e;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      max-width: 500px;
    }

    .bug-form label {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: #e6e6e6;
      font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .bug-form input,
    .bug-form textarea {
      margin-top: 6px;
      padding: 10px;
      background: #0d0d0d;
      border: 1px solid #2e2e2e;
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: #f2f2f2;
      font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .bug-form textarea {
      resize: vertical;
      min-height: 100px;
    }

    .bug-form button {
      padding: 10px 14px;
      background: #6a2cff;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: white;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 0.2s ease;
      font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .bug-form button:hover {
      background: #7b3dff;
    }

    /* ===== TABLES (NEW — MATCHES UI) ===== */
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-top: 16px;
      background: #1a1a1a;
      border: 1px solid #2e2e2e;
    }

    th, td {
      padding: 10px;
      border: 1px solid #2e2e2e;
      color: #e6e6e6;
      text-align: left;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    th {
      background: #2a2a2a;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #ffffff;
    }

    tr:nth-child(even) {
      background: #161616;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="page">

    <!-- Bug Report -->
    <section>
      <h2>Send a Bug Report</h2>
      <div class="section-content">

        <form action="https://formspree.io/f/mkolvdqw" method="POST" class="bug-form">

          <label>
            Your email:
            <input type="email" name="email" required>
          </label>

          <label>
            Bug description:
            <textarea name="message" required></textarea>
          </label>

          <button type="submit">Send Bug Report</button>

        </form>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What to expect -->
    <section>
      <h2>What to expect</h2>
      <div class="section-content">

        <p><strong>What it does</strong><br>
        Min4craft is a tiny simplified 4 pixel style resource pack that shrinks Minecraft’s textures down to a super minimal look. It keeps the game recognizable while giving it a bold, clean, low detail style.</p>

        <p><strong>Why you might want it</strong><br>
        You might want to try Min4craft if you like low resolution or just want Minecraft to look simple and lightweight. It doesn’t change gameplay.</p>

        <p><strong>Other information</strong><br>
        Pack is not fully finished — there are still a few bugs.</p>

        <table>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>16×16 Minecraft</th><th>4×4 Min4craft</th></tr>
          <tr><td>Detail</td><td>High detail, clear shapes</td><td>Extremely simplified, minimal shapes</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Color Variation</td><td>Many shades per block</td><td>Very few shades, flat colors</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Block Recognition</td><td>Easy to identify</td><td>Some blocks look similar due to low detail</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Item Clarity</td><td>Defined outlines</td><td>Items may lose detail or be hard to identify</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Performance</td><td>Normal performance</td><td>Slightly lighter due to tiny textures</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Style</td><td>Classic Minecraft look</td><td>Minimalistic, experimental</td></tr>
        </table>

        <p>This part was added to tell you what to expect and what changes, so you know what changes before using the pack.</p>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Don't waste time -->
    <section>
      <h2>Don't waste time</h2>
      <div class="section-content">

        <p><strong>What wasn't changed</strong><br>
        Fire, Lava, Chest, Ender Chest, Entities</p>

        <table>
          <tr><th>Texture</th><th>Status</th></tr>
          <tr><td>Fire</td><td>Not changed due to an error while changing texture</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lava</td><td>Not changed due to an error while changing texture</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Chest</td><td>Didn't get changed even when edited</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Ender Chest</td><td>Didn't get changed even when edited</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Entities</td><td>Didn't change</td></tr>
        </table>

        <p>This part was made to show you what wasn't changed so you don't waste time fixing something that was never edited.</p>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- License -->
    <section>
      <h2>License</h2>
      <div class="section-content">
        <p>This project is licensed under <strong>All Rights Reserved</strong>.<br>
          You may not redistribute, modify, or reupload the pack without permissions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <script>
    // Collapse/expand sections
    document.querySelectorAll("section h2").forEach((heading) => {
      heading.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const content = heading.nextElementSibling;
        const collapsed = heading.classList.toggle("collapsed");
        content.style.display = collapsed ? "none" : "block";
      });
    });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
